**[Tokenisation Isn’t the Revolution—The Rails Are](#)**  
The common narrative that tokenisation unlocks liquidity is misleading. Liquidity emerges when distribution, settlement and trust align on new infrastructure. Today’s tokenised assets still depend largely on legacy liquidity pools.  

The real innovation lies in the “rails”: programmable settlement, collateral mobility and continuous capital flows. Stablecoins exemplify this shift, acting as liquidity highways rather than new assets.  

Institutional adoption will be driven by balance sheet optimisation across repo, collateral and cross-border flows. Banks will remain central but repositioned as custodians and control layers. Ultimately, liquidity will follow the lowest-friction infrastructure. :contentReference[oaicite:2]{index=2}  

